(269, 1, '2022-05-04 16:46:48', '2022-05-04 16:46:48', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Razak brings a strong background in digital and social innovation and public policy to the development of patient engagement.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Passionate innovator and engineer, Razak held consulting, presales manager and product manager positions for 15 years within CAST, a software startup, working across Europe and the US.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>In 2012, Razak joined the French government, first as an advisor to the Minister for women’s rights and government spokeswoman and later as an advisor to the Minister for Education, Higher Education, and Research.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In charge of innovation and communication, Razak managed several digital projects related to women’s health, youth’s engagement, participative democracy, and social innovation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Beginning of 2018, Razak brought his experience to the Greater Paris University Hospitals (AP-HP) with the specific mission to increase patient engagement in medical research.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Working closely with patient organizations, researchers, and media, he has been instrumental in building one of the largest real-world evidence platform and patient participation community. During his tenure, 40,000 patients joined the “Communauté de Patients pour la Recherche” to participate in medical research on their chronic diseases thru patient-reported outcomes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Building from his experience,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/razakellafi/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Razak</a>&nbsp;is convinced of the power of collective intelligence and of the unique ability of patients to contribute to the future of healthcare. He joined admedicum to help both patient organizations and the industry build together better, higher and more sustainable value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Contact Razak</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>+33 6 24 49 26 24</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>razak.ellafi@admedicum.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/razakellafi/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">LinkedIn profile</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Razak Ellafi', 'Razak brings a strong background in digital and social innovation and public policy to the development of patient engagement.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'razak-ellafi', '', '', '2022-05-26 03:46:01', '2022-05-26 03:46:01', '', 0, 'http://admedicum.test/?post_type=empleados&#038;p=269', 0, 'empleados', '', 0),
(271, 1, '2022-05-04 18:03:15', '2022-05-04 18:03:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Robert is a patient advocate that has worked across four different EU countries. He is skilled at uniting international rare disease patient groups to address common goals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Robert is a rare disease patient advocate with over a decade\'s worth of experience in the healthcare field. He is originally from Chicago, USA and has been living in Europe since 2008.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He studied Psychology at University of Illinois where he focused on special education. After graduation, Robert led a group of adults with intellectual disabilities in a sheltered workshop environment. There he learned person-centered planning and the importance of getting to know the needs of each individual to assist them in succeeding.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a pivotal move in his life, Robert moved to Romania in 2008 with the United States Peace Corps where he served as an institutional development volunteer with the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.bolirareromania.ro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Romanian National Alliance for Rare Diseases</a>. There, Robert worked with one of his personal heroes and a cornerstone of rare disease patient advocacy in Romania, Dorica Dan, in creating a rare disease information center in Romania in partnership with the Norwegian organization,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.frambu.no/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Frambu</a>. Rob helped manage the complex, cross border project with the team and got to meet patients from a range of rare diseases. He assisted in advocating for the first National Plan for Rare Diseases in Romania after consultation with Alliance members.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next, Robert moved to Paris to join&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.eurordis.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">EURORDIS</a>-Rare Diseases Europe as the online patient communities’ manager where he worked for seven years. Along with Denis Costello, he co-founded&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.rareconnect.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">RareConnect.org</a>, the multilingual, global, online communities for rare diseases built in partnership with patient organizations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Robert had daily contact with people living with rare diseases and helped individuals break free from isolation while strengthening the relationships between international patient groups. Midway through his time with EURORDIS, he moved to Barcelona to help establish a new EURORDIS office there.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Robert speaks English, Romanian, French, and Spanish. He believes in putting patients’ needs first and the power of social media and new technologies to improve the lives of people living with rare diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Robert Pleticha', 'Robert is a patient advocate that has worked across four different EU countries. He is skilled at uniting international rare disease patient groups to address common goals.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'robert-pleticha', '', '', '2022-05-26 03:47:05', '2022-05-26 03:47:05', '', 0, 'http://admedicum.test/?post_type=empleados&#038;p=271', 0, 'empleados', '', 0),
(272, 1, '2022-05-04 18:05:18', '2022-05-04 18:05:18', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ulrike is educated as a health scientist and a medical assistant. She joined admedicum in September 2015. Beyond managing and executing various projects with a focus on patient engagement and patient access, she operates strategic and organizational processes within the company.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Experience</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>More than 12 years of experience in healthcare:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Over 4 years of working experience in conducting various projects relating to patient engagement and patient access for international pharmaceutical and medtech companies</li><li>Designing, developing and conducting interviews, round tables, focus groups, etc. with patients, caregivers, and HCPs</li><li>Transforming patients\' experiences into co-creation approaches and concrete business models</li><li>Experienced in compliant and transparent collaboration with patient organizations</li><li>More than 11 years of working experience in the health care sector including 8 years of working experience as a medical assistant in the fields of cardiology, general and internal medicine as well as surgery and emergency medicine</li><li>Experience in working with patients, relatives, and caregivers in various indications</li><li>Particular expertise in project management and organizational operations</li><li>Patient-oriented consultancy for the healthcare industry&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Education</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ulrike graduated with honors in Health Care Management (B.Sc.) at University of Applied Sciences, Krefeld (2015)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During her studies, she focused on e-health solutions and worked in different telemedicine centers as well as in emergency care.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thesis:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Konzeptionierung eines patientenorientierten Geschäftsmodells für ein App-basiertes telemedizinisches Betreuungsprogramm zur Gewichtsreduktion.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Research Projects:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Quantified Self - Einsatzmöglichkeiten mobiler Anwendungen als Basis für das Telemonitoring</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ulrike is educated as a Medical Assistant, Dresden (2010)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During her training and work experience, she worked in different in-patient and out-patient medical practices and medical centers in various indications with a focus on cardiology and internal medicine. Ulrike also gathered experience in the fields of general medicines, surgery, pulmonology, and emergency care. Furthermore, she gained skills in patient training, hygiene, and quality management.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Publications</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ulrike is author of many publications focusing mainly on patient-orientation in healthcare, especially in rare diseases, orphan drugs, and drug information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>German publications:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowak, U.; Reimann, A. (2016): Orphan Drugs – vom unmet need zur patientenrelevanten Therapie. In: Nanomagazin journal 10-9, 01/2016, S. 12-15.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowak, U.; Reimann, A. (206): Erfordernisse, Defizite und Gelingensbedingungen</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>patienten- zentrierter Versorgungsforschung bei Seltenen Erkrankungen. In: Kinder- und Jugendmedizin, 03/16, S. 192-198.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowak, U. (2016): Patientenbeauftragte in Unternehmen der pharmazeutischen</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Industrie: Ergebnisse der Unternehmensbefragung. admedicum ® Business for Patients GmbH &amp; Co KG., Köln</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reimann, A.; Nowak U. (2016): Patientenbeteiligung bei Ethik-Kommissionen: Probleme und Lösungswege. In: MEDIZIN-ETHIK - Forschungsethik und klinische Forschung: Zur Debatte um die EU-Verordnung zu klinischen Studien, Bd. 28, 2016, S. 37-41.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reimann, A.; von Gallwitz, P.; Harzheim, L.; Kolbe, K.; Nowak, U. (2018): Patientenorientierung in Pharmaunternehmen. In: Monitor Versorgungsforschung, Jg. 11, 01/18, S. 58-65.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Volunteer experience</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ulrike is educated as a Medical Assistant, Dresden (2010)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Ulrike Nowak', 'Ulrike is a doctor’s assistant with over 8 years of experience in the fields of cardiology, general and internal medicine and surgery. She graduated with honors in health care management.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ulrike-nowak', '', '', '2022-05-26 03:45:22', '2022-05-26 03:45:22', '', 0, 'http://admedicum.test/?post_type=empleados&#038;p=272', 0, 'empleados', '', 0),
(273, 1, '2022-05-04 18:07:05', '2022-05-04 18:07:05', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Christian holds a master’s degree in health economics. He joined admedicum in August 2018. Besides taking responsibility for general project management, he has deep experience in the measurement of patient preferences, conduction of patient dialogues and integration of patient insight into healthcare system optimization<strong>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Experience:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>More than 4 years of professional experience in the pharmaceutical sector<br>Familiar working with patients and physicians in various indications</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Experienced in the development and execution of patient dialogues</li><li>Good understanding of the German reimbursement system, including HTA processes</li><li>More than 2 years of working experience in the generic pharmaceutical industry. First as a Trainee Product Management, then as a Product and Market-Research Analyst</li><li>Further practical experiences at Institute for Quality and Efficiency in Health Care (IQWiG), University Hospital RWTH Aachen and Janssen-Cilag GmbH</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Education:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Christian graduated in Health Economics (M.Sc) at the University of Cologne in 2016. During his studies, he specialized in Medicine, Evidence-based Medicine and Health Technology Assessment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Master thesis:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-&nbsp;Development and validation of an Analytic-Hierarchy-Process (AHP) evaluation template<br>(Entwicklung und Validierung einer Analytic-Hierarchy-Process (AHP)-Auswertungsvorlage)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bachelor thesis:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-&nbsp;Determination of external validity for diagnostic accuracy studies<br>(Erfassung externer Validität bei diagnostischen Genauigkeitsstudien)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Selected research project:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-&nbsp;Incentives for an improved patient participation in the Joint Federal Committee<br>(Anreize für eine verbesserte Patientenbeteiligung im Gemeinsamen Bundesausschuss)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Publications:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-&nbsp;Danner M, Vennedey V, Hiligsmann M, Fauser S, Gross C, Stock S.; How Well Can Analytic Hierarchy Process be Used to Elicit Individual Preferences? Insights from a Survey in Patients Suffering from Age-Related Macular Degeneration. Patient. 2016 Oct;9(5):481-92.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>-&nbsp;Danner M, Vennedey V, Hiligsmann M, Fauser S, Gross C, Stock S.; Comparing Analytic Hierarchy Process and Discrete-Choice Experiment to Elicit Patient Preferences for Treatment Characteristics in Age-Related Macular Degeneration. Value Health. 2017 Sep;20(8):1166-1173.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>-&nbsp;Gutknecht M, Danner M, Schaarschmidt ML, Gross C, Augustin M.; Assessing the Importance of Treatment Goals in Patients with Psoriasis: Analytic Hierarchy Process vs. Likert Scales. Patient. 2018 Aug;11(4):425-437.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>-&nbsp;Sauerland S, Gross CTR.; Questions on randomized trials by Dionigi and coworkers. Langenbecks Arch Surg. 2019 Sep;404(Suppl 1):11-12.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Civilian service</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During his civilian service, Christian supported disabled people at the Lebenshilfe Aachen in their daily working routine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Christian Hoenig', 'Christian provides a very solid understanding and experience regarding the german pricing and reimbursement system to the team, including the importance of patient relevance data', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'christian-hoenig', '', '', '2022-05-26 03:44:47', '2022-05-26 03:44:47', '', 0, 'http://admedicum.test/?post_type=empleados&#038;p=273', 0, 'empleados', '', 0),
(274, 1, '2022-05-04 18:09:52', '2022-05-04 18:09:52', '<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Entrepreneur in the fields of patient-oriented health care and inclusive education</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Andreas is an entrepreneur in the fields of patient-oriented healthcare and inclusive education. He has trustworthy and deep connections with patient organizations and payers in Germany and Europe. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He understands the disruptive changes coming with Connected Health, and the role of patients and digital technology. Andreas had been a key contributor in numerous preparations of regulatory and health economic dossiers as a patient representative. He was a patient representative at the Federal Joint Committee (G-BA) in Germany for 11 years. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Andreas has a wife and two children and is the father of a boy living with Down syndrome. This too contributes to his conviction that the needs of patients and people living with disabilities should drive entrepreneurial decisions in the healthcare industry. He co-founded the company with Philipp von Gallwitz in 2015.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Education</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Andreas studied pharmacy in Frankfurt/Main and was state registered as a pharmacist in 1990. He earned a Ph.D. in Pharmacology from the Johann Wolfgang Goethe-University, Frankfurt/Main in 1995. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>His business studies included a minor degree in business administration from the German Distance-Learning University in Hagen in 1999 followed by an Executive program at the Netherlands Insitute of MBA-Studies (NIMBAS) in Utrecht, Bradford, Rouen and Mainz. He completed this 2-year program with a Master of Business Administration with distinction from the University of Bradford, UK in 2001.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Professional Experience since 1991</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Four years of academic research in pharmacology</li><li>7 ½ years in the pharmaceutical industry (clinical research, international marketing, drug information)</li><li>12 ½ years in a patient-organization (social support, patient-support, non-commercial clinical research, research promotion, quality management, research on health care, medical scientific information, fundraising) as chief executive officer of the German Cystic Fibrosis Association, Mukoviszidose e.V. and its professional affiliate for clinical research and quality management, Mukoviszidose Institut GmbH. During that time 11 years patient-representative at the Federal Joint Committee (G-BA), the major governing body in the German health-care system</li><li>Member of the Steering and Co-ordination committees of the National Action League for People with Rare Diseases (NAMSE), a patient and government-led multi stakeholder initiative spearheading Germany\'s first National Action Plan on Rare Diseases</li><li>Patient-oriented consultancy for the healthcare industry with admedicum since 2015</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Publications</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Andreas is the author of many publications and is giving lectures focusing mainly on patient-engagement and patient-access throughout the life-cycle of health-care products and services</li><li>Co-author of e-Learning Patient Engagement in Europe</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":327,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://admedicum.test/app/uploads/2022/05/articulo.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-327\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Volunteer experience</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Andreas is an active and passionate contributor in local government and in healthcare and education. Specifically:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Former Senior Vice President (2004 – 2014) and President (2014 – 2016) of the German Alliance for Rare Diseases (ACHSE)</li><li>Six years member of the board of directors of the EURORDIS- Rare Diseases Europe</li><li>Co-founder and Managing Director of the Offene Schule Köln, a privately-owned, state-recognized inclusive comprehensive school</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Dr. Andreas L.G. Reimann', 'Social entrepreneur in the fields of patient-oriented health care and inclusive education. He studied pharmacy, was state-registered as a pharmacist and earned a PhD in Pharmacology.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dr-andreas-l-g-reimann', '', '', '2022-05-26 03:45:01', '2022-05-26 03:45:01', '', 0, 'http://admedicum.test/?post_type=empleados&#038;p=274', 0, 'empleados', '', 0),
(275, 1, '2022-05-04 18:11:35', '2022-05-04 18:11:35', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Philipp has two decades of management experience in the innovative pharmaceutical industry. In addition to being a Co-founder and Managing Partner at admedicum, he is also a registered Attorney at Law in Cologne, Germany. This gives him additional expertise in legal compliance regarding industry-patients interactions.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He has a deep understanding of the role of patients as disruptive change-makers within pharmaceutical R&amp;D and innovation. He maintains a strong network among leading patient representatives in Europe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Philipp\'s extensive career includes 15 plus years in leadership roles at the private pharma company Grünenthal. There his work included searching for and evaluating late-stage specialty products in Europe. Philipp has in-depth experience with setting up structured approaches for patient engagement within pharma and biotech companies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He thoughtfully understands business value inflection points along the entire value chain of pharmaceutical development, be it in rare or common diseases or drug delivery, and how the patient view can make a difference at these junctions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He is the co-author of the online&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.patientengagement.guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www.patientengagement.guide</a>&nbsp;and the e-learning course&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.admedicum.com/en/news-details/e-learning-patient-engagement-in-europe\">Patient Engagement in Europe</a>. He has contributed to research in patient access as a co-author in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.admedicum.com/en/understanding-patients-needs-new?file=files/media/Videos/Poster%20V4%207th%20June%202019.pdf&amp;cid=2934\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Myopath study</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Philipp has three children with his wife. He knows disability and rare disease first hand from his one daughter who lives with severe disability due to a rare genetic neurodevelopmental disorder called CDKL5. Independently of his work with admedicum, he remains engaged in voluntary work with national and international patient/parent organizations and is a member of the EU IMI Patient Expert Pool. His belief that patient-oriented business thinking is one of the keys to future sustainable healthcare triggered his decision to co-found admedicum with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.admedicum.com/en/dr-andreas-l-g-reimann\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Andreas Reimann</a>&nbsp;in 2016.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Conctact:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>philipp.gallwitz@admedicum.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>+49 2236 94733 64 (60)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Philipp von Gallwitz', 'Philipp worked 20 years in pharma industry and worked closely with patients for a variety of purposes. He is a passionate advocate of patient engagement.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'philipp-von-gallwitz', '', '', '2022-05-26 03:45:37', '2022-05-26 03:45:37', '', 0, 'http://admedicum.test/?post_type=empleados&#038;p=275', 0, 'empleados', '', 0),
(276, 1, '2022-05-04 18:13:27', '2022-05-04 18:13:27', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Saskia acquired a broad medical know-how through her international biomedical studies ( B.Sc. \"Applied Life Sciences\" &amp; Ms.Sc. \"Biomedical Engineering\").<br>Afterwards she worked for some time in medical research with a focus on regenerative medicine.<br>&nbsp;<br>In addition, she worked for 14 years in the ambulance service and in medical and naturopathic practices. Therefore, she is not only experienced in working with patients, but also knows the German health care landscape very well.<br>&nbsp;<br>Saskia has been with admedicum since January 2021.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Saskia Zavelberg, M.Sc.', 'Saskia acquired a broad medical know-how through her international biomedical studies ( B.Sc. \"Applied Life Sciences\" & Ms.Sc. \"Biomedical Engineering\").', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'saskia-zavelberg-m-sc', '', '', '2022-05-26 03:41:49', '2022-05-26 03:41:49', '', 0, 'http://admedicum.test/?post_type=empleados&#038;p=276', 0, 'empleados', '', 0);
